Third-party methodology integration
-----------------------------------

The optional, off-by-default governance module (`taskctl/grace.mjs`, enabled
only when `grace.enabled` is set in taskctl.config.json) integrates with the
GRACE methodology — Graph-RAG Anchored Code Engineering — by Vladimir Ivanov
(osovv), https://github.com/osovv/grace-marketplace (MIT).

taskctl *wraps* GRACE; it does NOT vendor upstream GRACE code. `taskctl/grace.mjs`
is original taskctl code (the lint/XML gate, the prompt-hint and context-block
builders, and the sync-grace pipeline). The four GRACE subagent role files
(module-implementer, contract-reviewer, fixer, verification-reviewer) are NOT
included in this repository. You can verify both claims:

  - no vendored role files:  find . -iname '*grace-*-reviewer*'   (no results)
  - original wrapper:        inspect taskctl/grace.mjs

Attribution layering: the comment at the top of `taskctl/grace.mjs` is the
source-level provenance (crediting the upstream author in code); this NOTICE and
the README "Attribution" section are the distribution-facing credit. The
compliance fact is that no upstream GRACE source is vendored here — not a
line-count argument.
